\begin_inset Formula $U\ni s$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $V\ni s^{\prime}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $U\cap V=\varnothing$
\end_inset

.
 Why? Because 
\begin_inset Formula $\zeta\left(s\right)$
\end_inset

 is analytic.
 When a function 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(s\right)$
\end_inset

